        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Introduction\n",
        "\n",
        "Consumer reviews have long served as a cornerstone of business reputation and trust. In the digital age, the volume and velocity of online feedback has made manual analysis increasingly unsustainable, giving rise to the need for automated sentiment analysis.\n",
        "\n",
        "This report compares two NLP models for binary sentiment classification of women's e-commerce clothing reviews:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Evaluate **BERT** (encoder-based, discriminative) as a fine-tuned classification model\n",
        "- Evaluate **LLaMA3** (decoder-based, generative) using zero-shot prompting\n",
        "- Assess both models across key performance metrics: accuracy, F1-score, precision, and recall\n",
        "- Discuss business relevance, ethical considerations, and limitations for e-commerce deployment\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Methodology\n",
        "\n",
        "### Model Selection\n",
        "\n",
        "Two transformer-based NLP models were selected to reflect diferent approaches to Natural Language Understanding tasks:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Model | Type | Approach |\n",
        "|--------|---------|---------|\n",
        "| **BERT** | Encoder-based (discriminative) | Fine-tuned on labelled dataset via supervised learning |\n",
        "| **LLaMA3** | Decoder-based (generative) | Zero-shot prompting — no training or labelled examples required |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Dataset\n",
        "\n",
        "- Source: Kaggle — real-world women's e-commerce clothing reviews\n",
        "- ~23,500 records and 10 attributes prior to cleaning\n",
        "- Target variable: *Recommended IND* (binary: 1 = Recommended, 0 = Not Recommended)\n",
        "- Sentiment distribution: **82% Recommended / 18% Not Recommended** (imbalanced)\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Visualisation of Class Imbalance - Through Python"
      ],
      "id": "f6405dc0"
