        "### Data Preparation & Preprocessing\n",
        "\n",
        "- Null values in *Review Text* (845 total) were removed as this column functions as the model input\n",
        "- A stratified sample of **2,000 records** was extracted to preserve class distribution\n",
        "- Train/test split: **1,600 training / 400 test reviews** (80/20, random seed 42)\n",
        "- **Class weights** were applied to penalise misclassifications in the minority class (*Not Recommended*)\n",
        "- BERT tokenisation used WordPiece Tokenizer (30,522 tokens); truncation threshold set at **128 tokens** based on median review length analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "### Model Training & Prompting\n",
        "\n",
        "- **BERT** was fine-tuned using an **AdamW optimiser** (corrects weight decay issues present in standard Adam) at a learning rate of 2e-5 and batch size of 16, trained over **3 epochs**\n",
        "- **LLaMA3** was evaluated locally via zero-shot prompting using a structured prompt with three elements:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Prompt Element | Content |\n",
        "|---|---|\n",
        "| **Context** | You are classifying women's clothing reviews |\n",
        "| **Instruction** | Classify the review as either RECOMMENDED or NOT RECOMMENDED |\n",
        "| **Constraint** | Only reply with one of those two labels, nothing else |\n",
        "\n",
        "### Performance Metrics\n",
        "\n",
        "Accuracy, F1-score, precision, and recall were all assessed. Due to the class imbalance, accuracy alone is insufficient — it risks biasing the model toward the majority class, violating the EU's Trustworthy AI requirement of *Fairness*. F1-score was prioritised as the balance between precision and recall.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Summary of Findings\n",
        "\n",
        "### BERT Fine-Tuning\n",
        "\n",
        "Training loss declined consistently across all 3 epochs, demonstrating genuine learning rather than memorisation. Key loss comparisons:\n",
        "\n",
        "| | Starting Loss | Ending Loss | Loss Reduction |\n",
        "|---|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **1 Epoch** | 0.6186 | 0.3705 | 0.2461 |\n",
        "| **3 Epochs** | 0.5604 | 0.0174 | 0.5430 |\n",
        "\n",
        "- Training on 3 epochs yielded a loss reduction nearly **twice** that of 1 epoch\n",
        "- Some volatility remained at the 3rd epoch, suggesting scope for further refinement\n",
        "\n",
        "### BERT Evaluation Results\n",
        "\n",
        "BERT performed strongly for the majority class (*Recommended*) and respectably for the minority class (*Not Recommended*):\n",
        "\n",
        "| Metric | Recommended (1) | Not Recommended (0) | Macro Avg | Weighted Avg |\n",
        "|---|---|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **F1-Score** | 0.95 | 0.76 | 0.85 | 0.92 |\n",
        "| **Precision** | 0.94 | 0.80 | 0.87 | 0.92 |\n",
        "| **Recall** | 0.96 | 0.72 | 0.84 | 0.92 |\n",
        "\n",
        "- Precision outperforms recall for the minority class (0.80 vs 0.72) — the model accurately flags negatives but misses 28% of actual negatives\n",
        "- Overall accuracy: **91.75%**\n",
        "\n",
        "### LLaMA3 Zero-Shot Evaluation Results\n",
        "\n",
        "LLaMA3 demonstrated high recall for *Not Recommended* (0.97) but very low precision (0.57) — indicating it over-identifies negative reviews, classifying 43% as false positives:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Metric | Recommended (1) | Not Recommended (0) | Macro Avg | Weighted Avg |\n",
        "|---|---|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **F1-Score** | 0.91 | 0.72 | 0.81 | 0.87 |\n",
        "| **Precision** | 0.99 | 0.57 | 0.78 | 0.92 |\n",
        "| **Recall** | 0.83 | 0.97 | 0.90 | 0.86 |\n",
        "\n",
        "- Overall accuracy: **86.00%**\n",
        "- High recall bias toward *Not Recommended* likely a consequence of the absence of fine-tuning\n",
        "\n",
        "### Head-to-Head Comparison\n",
        "\n",
        "| Metric | BERT | LLaMA3 |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| **Overall Accuracy** | 91.75% | 86.00% |\n",
        "| **Macro F1** | 0.85 | 0.81 |\n",
        "| **Precision — Not Recommended** | 0.80 | 0.57 |\n",
        "| **Recall — Not Recommended** | 0.72 | 0.97 |\n",
        "| **Training Required** | Yes (30 min) | No |\n",
        "\n",
        "- BERT outperforms LLaMA3 across accuracy, Macro F1, and precision for negative sentiment\n",
        "- LLaMA3 achieves competitive results **without any training or labelled data**\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Discussion\n",
        "\n",
        "### Business Relevance\n",
        "\n",
        "- For e-commerce organisations, **LLaMA3** is the more accessible option — requiring no data labelling, training infrastructure, or deep technical knowledge\n",
        "- However, **BERT** is substantially more reliable at detecting genuine negative reviews, which carries real operational risk if misclassified (e.g. misdirected resources, unnecessary escalations)\n",
        "- A practical compromise is **DistilBERT** — a derivative of BERT operating at 97% of its capacity, 60% faster and 40% smaller — prioritising rapid deployment over exhaustive complexity\n",
        "\n",
        "### Ethics & Responsible AI\n",
        "\n",
        "- The dataset is anonymised and from an authentic source — consistent with EU Trustworthy AI requirements under *Privacy and Data Governance*\n",
        "- Class imbalance introduces bias risk, particularly violating the *Fairness* principle if the minority class is under-represented in training\n",
        "- LLaMA3's zero-shot bias toward negative classification raises additional concerns around reliability in production environments\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Recommendations\n",
        "\n",
        "The following directions are recommended for future work and deployment considerations:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Evaluate **DistilBERT** as a production-ready alternative to BERT — nearly equivalent performance at significantly lower resource cost\n",
        "- Explore **few-shot prompting** with LLaMA3 to assess whether providing examples improves precision for the minority class\n",
        "- Conduct **hyperparameter tuning** on BERT (learning rate, batch size, sample size) to address remaining volatility at epoch 3\n",
        "- Establish a **control group** (no class weights) to formally measure the impact of class weighting on model performance\n",
        "- Extend to **multi-class sentiment classification** to explore whether the metric uniformity observed in weighted averages persists across more than two labels\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "BERT demonstrated stronger and more balanced performance for the binary classification objective, with higher accuracy and more reliable detection of negative sentiment. LLaMA3's zero-shot results, while slightly weaker, highlight the growing potential of generative models for classification tasks — particularly in resource-constrained or low-expertise environments.\n",
